From: anytype-rtl <rtl@anytype-rtl.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Improve RTL support for numbered lists, toggles, and callouts

Enhances existing RTL support in the desktop app:
- Fix numbered list marker period placement (prevents ".1" instead of "1.")
- Mirror toggle arrow direction for RTL blocks
- Flip callout children padding for RTL

The detection and basic RTL infrastructure already exists (isRtl class,
direction: rtl, marker margin flip). This patch addresses the remaining
visual issues for Hebrew and Arabic content.

Ref: https://github.com/anyproto/anytype-ts/issues/757
---
 src/scss/block/common.scss | 7 +++++++
 src/scss/block/text.scss   | 9 +++++++++
 2 files changed, 16 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/scss/block/text.scss b/src/scss/block/text.scss
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/src/scss/block/text.scss
+++ b/src/scss/block/text.scss
@@ -37,6 +37,15 @@
 			.marker { margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 6px; }
 		}
+
+		/* Numbered markers: keep digit+period in LTR order to prevent ".1" instead of "1." */
+		.markers .marker.markerNumbered > span {
+			direction: ltr;
+			unicode-bidi: bidi-override;
+		}
 	}
+
+	/* Callout: flip children padding for RTL */
+	.block.blockText.textCallout.align2 > .wrapContent > .children { padding-left: 16px; padding-right: 0px; }
 }

diff --git a/src/scss/block/common.scss b/src/scss/block/common.scss
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/src/scss/block/common.scss
+++ b/src/scss/block/common.scss
@@ -113,6 +113,13 @@
 	.block.isToggled > .wrapContent > .selectionTarget > .dropTarget > .flex > .markers > .markerToggle { transform: rotateZ(90deg); }
+
+	/* RTL: mirror toggle arrow so collapsed state points left instead of right */
+	.block.align2 > .wrapContent > .selectionTarget > .dropTarget > .flex.isRtl > .markers > .markerToggle {
+		transform: scaleX(-1);
+	}
+	.block.align2.isToggled > .wrapContent > .selectionTarget > .dropTarget > .flex.isRtl > .markers > .markerToggle {
+		transform: scaleX(-1) rotateZ(90deg);
+	}

